Params: {1: '1', 3: "During the prolonged battle, her double-edged spear carves countless wounds. Blood, vital fluid, and whatever substance makes up Punishing creatures, all of it streams along the blade's groove and splashes toward the sky."}
{3: 'The spear, draped in red, twirls through the air leaving only a blur, like an eternal, unbroken circle.'}
{1: '1', 3: 'Until all of "Lloyd\'s" remains are destroyed, until Ephialtes lowers his head, falls to his knees, and his body gradually fades into transparency.'}
{3: 'Another empty vessel, driven by misguided heroism, fades away.'}
{3: 'He seems to drag his broken body back to the new world he had always longed for.'}
{3: 'Meanwhile, in a distant corner of the old world, someone seems to sense something and pauses the hand shuffling their cards.'}
{2: 'Lilith', 3: '...Just a leftover scrap from the card table, and yet with those broken remains, you actually dared to dream of igniting the flames that would destroy the old world?', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Lilith', 3: "I've never approved of that kind of spirit.", 4: '1'}
{3: 'She puts away her cards, ready to move on to the next location.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lilith', 3: "Anyway, I only lent a small hand. I'll just accept the loss and move on.", 4: '1'}
{3: 'But in the moment before leaving, she perceives new informationâ€”like a wisp of smoke slowly drifting across her tongue.'}
{2: 'Lilith', 3: 'Impressive indeed. They actually managed to cultivate controllable little bugs?', 4: '1'}
